Strange runes and pictographs, likely arcane in nature, have been scorched into the sides of this hide-covered strongbox.

A pair of sturdy guards that fit snug around your feet providing resistance to sweeping attacks by enemies. They didn't seem to do their last wearer much good though. When you first put your foot into your newly-found boots, you feel something lodged in the front of the left boot. Peering in, you note it's part of a dismembered foot...

Whatever enchantment these boots may hold, didn't seem to do their last wearer much good. When you first put your foot into your newly-found boots, you feel something lodged in the front of the left boot. Peering in, you note it's part of a foot...
When you first pick up these gloves, they're covered in some sort of mucus-like substance, fairly dripping with it. They'll likely need a good clean before you're willing to put your hand in there!

They're a bit yellowish at the edges due to age and there seems to be some hair sticking to them. From a dead adventurer? From the things he killed before they got him? Who cares... it's picked from a looted corpse so it must be useful, right?

This full plate seems to have been corroded here and there by some unknown substance. It doesn't seem to have affected the enchantment of protection it holds, but it does make it a bit trickier to move around in.
This full plate seems to have been corroded here and there by some unknown substance.

This shield seems to have taken quite a beating or rather, quite a clawing and biting. While there aren't any large dents in it, there are innumerable scratches from what must have been some rather vicious teeth and claws. It's still quite serviceable though.

This shield seems to have taken quite a beating or rather, quite a clawing and biting. While there aren't any large dents in it, there are innumerable scratches from what must have been some rather vicious teeth and claws. It's still quite serviceable though.

Clearly the bearer of this shield knew no fear when faced with Gibberlings. He seems to have stuck several of their claws and teeth right into the wood of his shield to be used for bashing! The presence of the noxious teeth however is not for the faint of heart.

This shield used to be completely round at one point, but looks to have suffered two rather devastating bites on each side which likely led to the previous owner's demise. It's still usable, if you don't mind the occasional splinter.

This chain shirt clearly has seen better days. There are a few links missing which seem to have been torn out by claws, likely the reason for the former owner's early death. Upon closer look there is a metal plate embedded in the upper chest area, carrying a rusty and blood stained symbol of Tyr.

As you first pick up the helm and turn it over in your hands, you note that it feels a bit heavier than it should. Then you realize why a moment later as you note two dead eyes staring back at you from the holes in the helm! It would seem that the helm did its job and protected the previous owner from getting his head caved in... but didn't help him keep it attached to his shoulders.

They're dusty, and you probably don't really want to know what that brownish goo is that's sticking to the glass. Also, it looks as if someone may have already sipped from them. But, hey, a bit of spittle won't kill you, will it? They'll likely still do the trick, healing some of your wounds.

Dusty Potion of Cure Serious Wounds

Clearly the last unfortunate wearer of these robes was ripped to shreds, if his clothing is any evidence. You know you'll fare better though, in fact, you find the open midriff of these torn robes to be quite freeing, if a bit chilly.

Seemingly more a chew toy for a Gibberling rather than a piece of armor, this set of leather has definitely seen better days. Every now and then you even catch yourself squashing what might be a small parasite trying to wriggle around in the armor.

This beautifully crafted belt is comprised of delicate looking links of chain that allow for a much greater mobility than some of the traditionally bulky and cumbersome belts adventurers seem to favour. It also seems to ground the wearer against electrical attacks.

This beautifully crafted belt is comprised of delicate looking links of chain that allow for a much greater mobility than some of the traditionally bulky and cumbersome belts adventurers seem to favour. It does seem to make you a bit better of a conductor however.

This cloak seems to have fared much better than other remnants you've found within the Maw. Though a bit faded from age and exposure, it doesn't seem to have been ravaged by the Gibberlings, likely due to the enchantments it holds.
This cloak seems to have fared much better than other remnants you've found within the Maw. Though a bit faded from age and exposure, it doesn't seem to have been ravaged by the Gibberlings.

Someone has gotten creative and made a sort of charm or talisman out of the bones of Gibberlings. You're not sure how, but it seems to help ward off the creatures and provide some protection against their filthy bites.
Someone has gotten creative and made a sort of charm or talisman out of the bones of Gibberlings.

A very crude dagger made entirely of bone, little more than a shard of sharpened bone in fact. It is however coated with a great deal of slimy substances which look a little bit caustic and lot like drool and can fly hazardously from the blade if flicked just right.

A very crude dagger made entirely of bone, little more than a shard of sharpened bone in fact. It is however coated with a bit of a slimy substance which looks somewhat caustic... and somewhat like drool.

The durability of the Ironwood this club has been made from seems to have made it less-than-desirable as a chew toy for the Gibberlings here. The thin coating of slime on it seems to indicate it didn't stop them from trying though. A deft flick of the club can throw off some of this slime towards the feet of your enemies, sometimes sticking them in place.

This metal seems to have been purposely blackened by continuous exposure to open flame. Some of the heat still radiates from the blade, indicating the flame was likely magical. Striking the blade with a block of flint causes the sparks to flare into heated volleys of flame.

Left in a puddle in the Gibberling tunnels for far too long, the metal of this longsword has long since corroded. It's still quite usable though, and carries a nasty extra little sting now. In trying to scrape corrosion from the blade, bursts of negative energy are freed from the blade's turbulent core.

You can only assume that some poor adventurer dropped his sword in one of those peculiar but deadly clouds of chaos and that it froze from exposure. When brandished with chilling intent, an ice crystal that has formed where guards meets pommel can eject the chaotic cold.
